{"count": 28681, "next": "https://api.acmi.net.au/creators/?page=1791", "previous": "https://api.acmi.net.au/creators/?page=1789", "results": [{"id": 26582, "name": "Gene Saks", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 1989130, "title": "Mame", "work_id": 85053, "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 2108082, "title": "Barefoot in the park", "work_id": 85009, "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 1988503, "title": "The Odd couple", "work_id": 84626, "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "", "date_of_birth": "1921-11-08", "date_of_death": "2015-03-28", "genders": [{"id": 9, "name": "Male", "slug": "male"}], "languages": [{"id": 1, "name": "English", "slug": "english"}], "places_of_operation": [{"id": 1, "name": "United States of America", "slug": "united-states-of-america"}], "biography": "Gene Saks (born Jean Michael Saks; November 8, 1921 – March 28, 2015) was an American director and actor.  An inductee of the American Theater Hall of Fame, his acting career began with a Broadway debut in 1949.  As a director, he was nominated for seven Tony Awards, winning three for his direction of I Love My Wife, Brighton Beach Memoirs and Biloxi Blues.  He also directed a number of films during his career.  He was married to Bea Arthur from 1950 until 1978, and subsequently to Keren Saks from 1980 to his death in 2015.\n\n", "biography_author": "Wikidata", "date_of_biography": "2022-05-19T11:34:09.064865+10:00", "external_links": [{"id": 2101, "uri": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gene_Saks"}], "uuid": "c0007945-8de7-4936-a865-d4ddbdee87e5", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "19478", "external_references": [{"id": 9064, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q1388109"}, {"id": 9065, "source": {"name": "VIAF", "slug": "viaf"}, "source_identifier": "114957215"}, {"id": 9066, "source": {"name": "LOC Auth", "slug": "loc-auth"}, "source_ident